        "title": "MySql STR_TO_DATE not working in Stored Procedure",
        "body": "<p>I want to add date from my JSP to mysql database using Servlet, if i write a query then STR_TO_DATE work properly for insertion, but if i use STR_TO_DATE in Stored Procedure it gives me \"com.mysql.jdbc.MysqlDataTruncation: Data truncation: Incorrect date value: '11-10-2015' for column 'DATE' at row 1\".<\/p>\n\n<p>My Query is:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>INSERT INTO TABLENAME (DATE) VALUES (STR_TO_DATE('01/01/2010','%d-%m-%Y'));\" \n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Any Idea?<\/p>\n",
